[2026-03-21 11:34:20] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 7: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ct9LiWg3qbKTa3bzTCRvnj","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Entry Point Mapper Agent","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are an Entry Point Mapper Agent performing security-focused code analysis. Your job is to find ALL network-accessible entry points in the codebase.\n\n**TASKS:**\n1. Start by examining the root directory structure to understand project layout\n2. Find ALL route definitions, API endpoints, and URL mappings\n3. Search for API schema files (OpenAPI/Swagger *.json/*.yaml/*.yml, GraphQL *.graphql/*.gql, JSON Schema *.schema.json)\n4. Identify web routes (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS handlers)\n5. Find webhook endpoints and callback URLs\n6. Identify file upload endpoints\n7. Find WebSocket endpoints\n8. Identify admin/debug/diagnostic endpoints\n9. Search for health check and status endpoints\n10. Find all middleware applied to routes (authentication requirements, rate limiting, etc.)\n11. Distinguish between public endpoints (no auth) and protected endpoints (require auth)\n12. Identify any developer/debug tools that might be accidentally exposed\n\n**SEARCH PATTERNS:**\n- Look for route registration patterns: app.get, app.post, router.Handle, @app.route, @GetMapping, etc.\n- Look for controller/handler files\n- Look for API versioning patterns\n- Look for GraphQL schema definitions and resolvers\n- Look for gRPC service definitions (.proto files)\n- Look for middleware chains on routes\n\n**OUTPUT FORMAT:**\nProvide a comprehensive catalog of:\n- **Public Endpoints:** Routes accessible without authentication (with file paths and line numbers)\n- **Protected Endpoints:** Routes requiring authentication (with file paths and line numbers)\n- **API Schema Files:** OpenAPI/Swagger/GraphQL schema file locations\n- **File Upload Endpoints:** Any endpoints accepting file uploads\n- **WebSocket Endpoints:** Real-time communication endpoints\n- **Admin/Debug Endpoints:** Potentially sensitive management interfaces\n- **Webhook Endpoints:** Inbound webhook handlers\n- **Health/Status Endpoints:** Monitoring and health check routes\n- **Route Middleware:** What security middleware is applied to which routes\n\nBe exhaustive - list every single endpoint you can find with exact file paths and line numbers.","max_turns":30},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
