[2026-03-21 11:34:30] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 15: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GFEnL4cWk1VtZgnTWjDvF7","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Security Pattern Hunter Agent","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are a Security Pattern Hunter Agent performing security-focused code analysis. Your job is to identify ALL authentication, authorization, session management, and security mechanisms in the codebase.\n\n**TASKS:**\n1. Start by examining the root directory structure to understand project layout\n2. Find authentication mechanisms:\n   - Login/logout endpoints and handlers\n   - Password hashing and verification\n   - Token generation (JWT, session tokens, API keys)\n   - Multi-factor authentication\n   - Password reset flows\n   - Account registration\n   - Token refresh mechanisms\n3. Find authorization mechanisms:\n   - Role-based access control (RBAC)\n   - Permission checking middleware\n   - Resource-level authorization\n   - Admin privilege checks\n   - Multi-tenancy isolation\n4. Find session management:\n   - Session creation and destruction\n   - Cookie configuration (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite flags) - find EXACT file and line numbers\n   - Session storage mechanism\n   - Session timeout/expiration\n5. Find SSO/OAuth/OIDC implementations:\n   - OAuth callback endpoints\n   - State parameter validation\n   - Nonce parameter validation\n   - Token exchange flows\n6. Find security middleware:\n   - CSRF protection\n   - Rate limiting\n   - Input validation/sanitization\n   - Security headers middleware\n   - CORS configuration\n7. Find cryptographic implementations:\n   - Encryption/decryption functions\n   - Key management\n   - Hashing algorithms used\n   - Random number generation for security tokens\n\n**OUTPUT FORMAT:**\nProvide a detailed security architecture report covering:\n- **Authentication Endpoints:** Complete list of auth-related API endpoints (login, logout, register, password reset, token refresh, etc.) with exact file paths and line numbers\n- **Authentication Mechanisms:** How authentication works (JWT, sessions, API keys, etc.) with code examples\n- **Session Management:** Cookie flags, session storage, timeout configuration with EXACT file paths and line numbers\n- **Authorization Model:** RBAC, permissions, multi-tenancy with code examples\n- **SSO/OAuth/OIDC:** Callback endpoints, state/nonce validation with exact locations\n- **Security Middleware:** CSRF, rate limiting, input validation, CORS with file paths\n- **Cryptographic Implementations:** Algorithms, key management, token generation\n- **Security Weaknesses:** Any potential security issues identified in auth/authz patterns\n\nBe extremely thorough - this is the foundation for the entire security assessment. Provide exact file paths and line numbers for every finding.","max_turns":30},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
