[2026-03-21 11:48:00] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 229: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BYzSY6K3jfYdyksxjwP5V6","name":"mcp__shannon-helper__save_deliverable","input":{"deliverable_type":"RECON","content":"# Architecture Security Scan Report: KamriHub Web (kamri-web)\n\n## 1. Technology Stack\n\n### Primary Languages & Frameworks\n| Technology | Version | File | Security Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Next.js** | 14.2.33 | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json` | App Router pattern. Version 14.2.x is current-ish but should be monitored for patches. |\n| **React** | ^18.0.0 | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json` | Client-side rendering with SSR. |\n| **TypeScript** | ^5.0.0 | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json` | `strict: false` in tsconfig -- reduces type safety. |\n| **Tailwind CSS** | ^3.0.0 | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json` | UI framework, no direct security impact. |\n| **Zod** | ^3.25.76 | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/packages/lib/package.json` | Schema validation library -- used in shared lib for validation schemas. |\n\n### Key Dependencies with Security Implications\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose | Security Relevance |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **@stripe/stripe-js** | ^2.0.0 | Stripe payment integration | Payment processing -- PCI-DSS scope. Client-side only (publishable key). |\n| **@stripe/react-stripe-js** | ^2.0.0 | Stripe React components | Payment UI elements. |\n| **multer** | ^2.0.2 | File upload middleware | File upload handling in API routes -- potential for arbitrary file upload. |\n| **framer-motion** | ^12.23.24 | Animation library | No direct security concern. |\n| **zod** | ^3.25.76 | Validation | Used in `@kamri/lib` for input validation schemas. |\n| **lucide-react** | ^0.545.0 | Icons | No security concern. |\n\n### Internal Packages (Monorepo)\n| Package | Path | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| **@kamri/lib** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/packages/lib/` | Shared types, API client, validation schemas (Zod), utilities. |\n| **@kamri/ui** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/packages/ui/` | Shared UI components (React). |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Architectural Pattern\n\n**Pattern:** Monolithic Next.js frontend (App Router) communicating with a separate backend API (NestJS on Railway).\n\n**Frontend (this repo):**\n- Next.js 14 App Router with Server Components and Client Components\n- Locale-based routing: `/[locale]/...` (fr, en)\n- API proxy routes within Next.js (`/api/*`)\n- Deployed to Vercel (CDG1 region -- Paris)\n\n**Backend (external, NOT in this repo):**\n- NestJS server hosted on Railway (`kamri-server-production.up.railway.app`)\n- API prefix: `/api`\n- Handles: auth (JWT + OTP + Google OAuth), products, cart, orders, payments (Stripe), shipping (CJDropshipping), reviews, addresses, settings, invoices, disputes, geo, tracking\n\n**CMS (external):**\n- Strapi CMS for campaign management (optional, toggled via `useStrapi` setting)\n- Strapi image proxy through Next.js API routes\n\n**Third-party services:**\n- **Stripe** -- Payment processing (client-side Elements + server-side PaymentIntent)\n- **Google Maps/Places API** -- Address autocomplete\n- **Google OAuth** -- Social login (delegated to backend)\n- **CJDropshipping** -- Dropshipping fulfillment, logistics, disputes\n- **Supabase** -- Storage for user avatars (optional, with fallback to Railway backend)\n- **Google Analytics / Plausible / PostHog** -- Analytics (with Consent Mode v2)\n\n### Trust Boundaries\n```\n[Browser Client] <--HTTPS--> [Vercel CDN/Edge (Next.js)] <--HTTPS--> [Railway Backend API]\n                                    |                                        |\n                                    |--- /api/avatar/* (SSRF proxy) -------> [Supabase Storage / Backend uploads]\n                                    |--- /api/strapi-image/* (SSRF proxy) -> [Strapi CMS]\n                                    |--- /api/stripe/config (config leak) -> [env vars]\n                                    |\n[Browser] <--HTTPS--> [Stripe.js CDN] <--HTTPS--> [Stripe API]\n[Browser] <--HTTPS--> [Google Maps API]\n[Browser] <--HTTPS--> [Google OAuth (via backend redirect)]\n```\n\n**Key trust boundaries:**\n1. **Browser <-> Vercel Edge (middleware):** CSP headers, locale routing, maintenance mode bypass\n2. **Vercel <-> Railway Backend:** JWT Bearer auth for protected endpoints; no auth for public endpoints\n3. **Next.js API routes as SSRF proxies:** `/api/avatar/[...path]` and `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` fetch arbitrary paths from backend/Strapi -- SSRF risk\n4. **Auth token storage:** JWT stored in localStorage (with memory cache layer) -- accessible to XSS\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Files\n\n| File | Path | Security Relevance |\n|---|---|---|\n| **package.json** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json` | Dependency manifest. Version ranges (^) allow minor/patch auto-updates. |\n| **package-lock.json** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package-lock.json` | Pinned dependency versions. Present -- good for reproducible builds. |\n| **next.config.js** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/next.config.js` | CSP headers, image remote patterns (allows ALL hosts `**`), console removal in prod. |\n| **tsconfig.json** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/tsconfig.json` | `strict: false` -- reduces TypeScript safety guarantees. |\n| **tailwind.config.js** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/tailwind.config.js` | UI config only. |\n| **vitest.config.ts** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/vitest.config.ts` | Test configuration. |\n| **vercel.json** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/vercel.json` | Deployment config with security headers, CORS for `/api/*`, and region pinning. |\n| **.env.local** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/.env.local` | **COMMITTED TO REPO** -- Contains Google Maps API key (`AIzaSyCtlI5rM3SYATTYTHhbKXgCcTkK7B44sbE`). |\n| **.gitignore** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/.gitignore` | Lists `.env*.local` but `.env.local` IS tracked in git (inconsistency or override). |\n| **public/manifest.json** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/public/manifest.json` | PWA manifest. `display: standalone`. |\n| **middleware.ts** | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts` | Edge middleware: CSP, security headers, locale routing, maintenance bypass, host redirect. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Infrastructure & Deployment\n\n### Hosting\n- **Frontend:** Vercel (region `cdg1` -- Paris, France)\n- **Backend API:** Railway (`kamri-server-production.up.railway.app`)\n- **CMS:** Strapi (configurable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL`)\n- **Storage:** Supabase (optional, for avatars)\n\n### Vercel Configuration (`vercel.json`)\n- Build command: `npm run build`\n- Framework: Next.js\n- Region: `cdg1` (Paris)\n- Security headers applied to all routes (`/(.*)`):\n  - `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`\n  - `X-Frame-Options: DENY`\n  - `X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block`\n  - `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`\n  - `Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()`\n  - `Content-Security-Policy` (Stripe + Google Maps whitelisted)\n- `/api/*` routes have `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` (wide-open CORS)\n- `/admin/*` routes have `X-Robots-Tag: noindex, nofollow`\n\n### Notable: No HSTS header\n- `Strict-Transport-Security` is NOT configured anywhere in the codebase (middleware, next.config.js, or vercel.json).\n- Vercel provides HTTPS by default but HSTS preload is not set.\n\n### No Dockerfile/docker-compose\n- No containerization configs found in this repo.\n- No CI/CD pipeline (`.github/workflows/` directory does not exist).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Security Headers Configuration\n\nSecurity headers are configured in THREE places (potential inconsistency):\n\n### A. Middleware (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`)\n```\nContent-Security-Policy: [full CSP with Stripe + Google Maps + accounts.google.com missing in middleware vs next.config.js]\nX-Frame-Options: DENY\nX-Content-Type-Options: nosniff\nReferrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin\nX-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off\nPermissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()\n```\n\n### B. next.config.js (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/next.config.js`)\n```\nContent-Security-Policy: [includes accounts.google.com in script-src -- different from middleware]\n```\nApplied to `/:path*`.\n\n### C. vercel.json (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/vercel.json`)\n```\nX-Content-Type-Options: nosniff\nX-Frame-Options: DENY\nX-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block\nReferrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin\nPermissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()\nContent-Security-Policy: [yet another CSP variant -- missing Google Maps in connect-src]\n```\n\n### CSP Analysis (Critical Issues):\n- **`unsafe-inline` + `unsafe-eval` in script-src:** Required by Next.js runtime but significantly weakens CSP. No nonce-based CSP is implemented.\n- **`img-src 'self' data: https: http:`** -- Allows images from ANY origin including HTTP (mixed content risk).\n- **`font-src 'self' data: https:`** -- Allows fonts from any HTTPS origin.\n- **Three different CSP definitions** across middleware, next.config.js, and vercel.json -- risk of inconsistency and bypasses.\n- **Missing `Strict-Transport-Security` (HSTS)** -- Not set anywhere.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Dependency Analysis\n\n### Security-Relevant Findings\n\n1. **multer ^2.0.2** (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/package.json`): File upload middleware. Used in the project (imported as type in `@types/multer`). The contact form supports file attachments via `FormData`.\n\n2. **zod ^3.25.76** (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/packages/lib/package.json`): Validation schemas defined for Product, User, CartItem, Order, Address. However, these schemas are in the shared lib and may not be applied consistently at all API boundaries.\n\n3. **DOMPurify** (optional, not in package.json): Referenced in `src/utils/sanitize.ts` via `window.DOMPurify` but NOT listed as a dependency. The sanitization falls back to regex-based HTML escaping, which is less robust.\n\n4. **No CSRF protection library**: No csrf tokens or double-submit cookie patterns visible in the frontend.\n\n5. **No rate limiting library (server-side)**: The `src/lib/rateLimiter.ts` is explicitly labeled \"frontend soft\" rate limiting using localStorage -- trivially bypassable.\n\n### Environment Variables Referenced\n| Variable | Exposure | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | Client-exposed | Backend API URL |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Client-exposed | Stripe publishable key |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` | Client-exposed, **committed in .env.local** | Google Maps API key |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL` | Client-exposed | Strapi CMS URL |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` | Client-exposed | Site canonical URL |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLIC_URL` | Client-exposed | Supabase storage URL |\n| `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Server-only | Stripe key (fallback) |\n| `API_URL` / `KAMRI_API_URL` | Server-only | Backend API URL (SSR) |\n| `SUPABASE_PUBLIC_URL` | Server-only | Supabase storage |\n| `MAINTENANCE_MODE` | Server-only | Maintenance toggle |\n| `MAINTENANCE_BYPASS_CODE` | Server-only | Maintenance bypass (hardcoded default: `dev-bypass-2024`) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Build/Deploy Pipeline\n\n### Build System\n- **Build:** `next build` (via `npm run build`)\n- **Dev:** `next dev`\n- **Testing:** Vitest (unit tests in `src/__tests__/` and `src/**/*.test.ts`)\n- **Linting:** ESLint with `eslint-config-next`\n- **Type checking:** `tsc --noEmit`\n- **Playwright** in devDependencies (E2E testing capability)\n\n### Deployment\n- **Platform:** Vercel (configured via `vercel.json`)\n- **No CI/CD pipeline** (no `.github/workflows/`, no `.gitlab-ci.yml`, no `Jenkinsfile`)\n- **No automated security scanning** (no Snyk, Dependabot, or similar configured)\n- **Postinstall script** installs sub-package dependencies (`packages/lib` and `packages/ui`)\n\n### Scripts\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dev` | `next dev` | Development server |\n| `build` | `next build` | Production build |\n| `start` | `next start` | Production server |\n| `lint` | `next lint` | ESLint |\n| `type-check` | `tsc --noEmit` | TypeScript checking |\n| `test` | `vitest run` | Unit tests |\n| `sitemap:generate` | `node scripts/generate-sitemap.js` | Sitemap generation |\n| `sitemap:ping` | `node scripts/ping-sitemap.js` | Ping search engines |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Authentication & Authorization Architecture\n\n### Authentication Methods\n1. **Email/Password login** -- `POST /api/auth/login` returns `access_token` (JWT)\n2. **OTP (email)** -- `POST /api/auth/request-otp` + `POST /api/auth/verify-otp`\n3. **Google OAuth** -- Redirect to backend `/api/auth/google`, callback at `/auth/google/callback` receives token via URL query/hash param\n4. **Registration** -- `POST /api/auth/register`\n\n### Token Management (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/secureToken.ts`)\n- JWT stored in memory (primary) + localStorage (persistence after reload)\n- Token key: `auth_token` in localStorage\n- Client-side JWT expiration check (payload only, no signature verification)\n- 24-hour session max duration (timestamp-based)\n- Auto-cleanup on 401 responses\n\n### Authorization\n- **Admin page** (`/admin/`) has no client-side auth guard -- just a placeholder page with `noindex/nofollow` metadata. No role check visible.\n- **Protected API calls** use `fetchWithAuth()` which attaches `Bearer` token. 401 responses trigger token cleanup.\n- **No RBAC enforcement visible** on the frontend -- role-based access control would need to be enforced by the backend.\n\n### Google OAuth Callback Security (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx`)\n- Token received via URL query parameter or hash fragment\n- Token stored immediately via `setAuthToken()` (localStorage)\n- Return URL stored in `sessionStorage` (`google_auth_return_url`) -- potential open redirect if backend doesn't validate callback URL\n- `safeRedirect()` utility exists (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/security/safeRedirect.ts`) for preventing open redirects -- validates paths start with `/` and rejects absolute URLs and `//`\n\n---\n\n## 9. API Proxy Routes (SSRF Surface)\n\n### `/api/avatar/[...path]` (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts`)\n- Accepts arbitrary path segments\n- Attempts Supabase candidates first, then falls back to backend `/uploads/users/{path}`\n- **SSRF risk:** The `path` parameter is user-controlled and joined directly into URLs\n- Returns `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`\n\n### `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts`)\n- Accepts arbitrary path segments AND a `?id=` query parameter\n- Fetches from Strapi API (`/api/upload/files/{id}`) and direct URL paths\n- Also searches by filename via `filters[name][$contains]=`\n- **SSRF risk:** User-controlled path and ID parameters are used to construct fetch URLs\n- Returns `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`\n- **Information disclosure:** Extensive `console.log`/`console.error` in production (though console.log removed by compiler in prod)\n\n### `/api/stripe/config` (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/stripe/config/route.ts`)\n- Returns Stripe publishable key from server environment\n- No authentication required\n- Publishable keys are public by design, but this endpoint exposes server env var configuration\n\n### `/api/analyze-product` (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/analyze-product/route.ts`)\n- No authentication required\n- Accepts product ID via query parameter\n- Returns detailed variant analysis -- potential information disclosure\n\n---\n\n## 10. Input Validation & XSS Prevention\n\n### Sanitization (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/sanitize.ts`)\n- `sanitizeHtml()` uses DOMPurify if available, falls back to regex-based escaping\n- DOMPurify is NOT in `package.json` -- relies on it being loaded externally via `window.DOMPurify`\n- The regex fallback re-allows certain tags after escaping -- potential bypass\n\n### Validation (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/validation.ts`)\n- Input validators for phone, city, state, zip, country, street\n- `sanitizeText()` strips HTML tags and control characters\n- Applied to address forms\n\n### Anti-Spam (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/antiSpam.ts`)\n- Honeypot field validation\n- Minimum time delay check (1200ms)\n- Spam text detection (URLs, known spam keywords)\n- Client-side only -- bypassable\n\n### `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` Usage\nFound in 4 files:\n1. `src/app/layout-scripts.tsx` -- Google Consent Mode initialization (controlled content)\n2. `src/app/[locale]/product/[slug]/ProductJsonLd.tsx` -- JSON-LD structured data\n3. `src/app/[locale]/product/[slug]/BreadcrumbJsonLd.tsx` -- JSON-LD structured data\n4. `src/components/CategoryItemListJsonLd.tsx` -- JSON-LD structured data\n\nJSON-LD components may inject product data from API responses into `<script type=\"application/ld+json\">` -- if product names/descriptions contain malicious content from the backend, this could be exploited.\n\n---\n\n## 11. GDPR / Privacy Compliance\n\n- **Cookie consent system** (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/cookieConsent.ts`): Granular consent (necessary, analytics, marketing)\n- **Google Consent Mode v2** (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/googleConsentMode.ts`): Default-denied, updated based on user consent\n- **Analytics layer** (`/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/analytics.ts`): Respects consent for marketing events; technical events (auth, checkout) always tracked\n- **Cookie banner** component exists\n- **IP anonymization** in GA4 events\n\n---\n\n## 12. Critical Security Findings Summary\n\n| # | Finding | Severity | Location |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | **SSRF via image proxy routes** -- user-controlled paths in `/api/avatar/[...path]` and `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` can be used to make server-side requests to arbitrary internal/external URLs | HIGH | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts`, `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts` |\n| 2 | **JWT in localStorage** -- auth tokens stored in localStorage are accessible to any XSS payload; memory-first approach only partially mitigates (still synced to localStorage) | HIGH | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/secureToken.ts` |\n| 3 | **CSP allows unsafe-inline + unsafe-eval** -- significantly weakens XSS protection; three inconsistent CSP definitions across middleware, next.config.js, and vercel.json | HIGH | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`, `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/next.config.js`, `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/vercel.json` |\n| 4 | **Next.js image optimization allows ALL remote hosts** (`hostname: \"**\"` for both HTTP and HTTPS) | MEDIUM | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/next.config.js` |\n| 5 | **Google Maps API key committed in .env.local** | MEDIUM | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/.env.local` |\n| 6 | **Maintenance bypass code has hardcoded default** (`dev-bypass-2024`) | MEDIUM | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts` |\n| 7 | **No HSTS header configured** | MEDIUM | All header config locations |\n| 8 | **Wide-open CORS on /api/* routes** (`Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`) | MEDIUM | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/vercel.json` |\n| 9 | **DOMPurify not installed** -- sanitization falls back to regex-based approach | MEDIUM | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/sanitize.ts` |\n| 10 | **No CI/CD security pipeline** -- no automated dependency scanning, SAST, or DAST | MEDIUM | Project root |\n| 11 | **TypeScript strict mode disabled** (`strict: false`) | LOW | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/tsconfig.json` |\n| 12 | **Admin page has no auth guard** -- placeholder only, but route exists | LOW | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/admin/page.tsx` |\n| 13 | **Frontend-only rate limiting** (localStorage-based, trivially bypassable) | LOW | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/rateLimiter.ts` |\n| 14 | **Google OAuth token passed via URL parameter** -- may be logged in server/CDN access logs | LOW | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` |\n\n---\n\n## 13. Application Route Map\n\n### Public Pages (no auth required)\n- `/[locale]/` -- Homepage\n- `/[locale]/categories/` -- Category listing\n- `/[locale]/categories/[slug]/` -- Category detail\n- `/[locale]/product/[slug]/` -- Product detail\n- `/[locale]/products/` -- Product listing\n- `/[locale]/search/` -- Search\n- `/[locale]/contact/` -- Contact form\n- `/[locale]/legal/`, `/[locale]/privacy/`, `/[locale]/terms/`, `/[locale]/returns/` -- Legal pages\n- `/[locale]/promotions/` -- Promotions\n- `/[locale]/auth/` -- Auth page\n- `/[locale]/auth/google/callback/` -- Google OAuth callback\n\n### Protected Pages (auth required, client-side check)\n- `/[locale]/profile/` -- User profile\n- `/[locale]/favorites/` -- Wishlist\n- `/[locale]/cart/` -- Shopping cart\n- `/[locale]/checkout/` -- Checkout (Stripe)\n- `/[locale]/order-confirmation/` -- Order confirmation\n- `/[locale]/account/orders/[id]/` -- Order detail\n- `/[locale]/invoices/[id]/download/` -- Invoice download\n\n### Admin Pages\n- `/[locale]/admin/` -- Admin placeholder (noindex, no auth guard)\n\n### API Routes (Next.js)\n- `/api/analyze-product` -- Product analysis (no auth)\n- `/api/avatar/[...path]` -- Avatar image proxy (no auth)\n- `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` -- Strapi image proxy (no auth)\n- `/api/stripe/config` -- Stripe config (no auth)\n- `/robots.txt` -- Dynamic robots.txt\n- `/sitemap.xml`, `/sitemap-categories.xml`, `/sitemap-pages.xml`, `/sitemap-products-[id]` -- Dynamic sitemaps\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
