[2026-03-21 11:50:54] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 246: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CvtacTDRYk6LF8CHxhANqH","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Examine root directory structure and project layout","status":"completed","activeForm":"Examining root directory structure and project layout"},{"content":"Find authentication mechanisms (login, logout, tokens, password flows)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding authentication mechanisms"},{"content":"Find authorization mechanisms (RBAC, permissions, middleware)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding authorization mechanisms"},{"content":"Find session management (cookies, storage, timeouts)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding session management"},{"content":"Find SSO/OAuth/OIDC implementations","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding SSO/OAuth/OIDC implementations"},{"content":"Find security middleware (CSRF, rate limiting, CORS, headers)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding security middleware"},{"content":"Find cryptographic implementations","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding cryptographic implementations"},{"content":"Compile security architecture report","status":"completed","activeForm":"Compiling security architecture report"}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
[2026-03-21 11:51:42] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 247: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DWAhzYwcaniTcYHNNxHpxD","name":"mcp__shannon-helper__save_deliverable","input":{"deliverable_type":"CODE_ANALYSIS","content":"# Entry Point Map -- KamriHub/kamri-web (Next.js 15 App Router)\n\n## Project Overview\n- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router) with TypeScript\n- **Architecture:** Client-side rendered e-commerce frontend (SPA-like). The Next.js server hosts route handlers that proxy to a separate backend API (`kamri-server`) and serve SEO artifacts (sitemaps, robots.txt). Authentication is JWT-based via a separate backend; the frontend stores tokens in localStorage/memory.\n- **Backend API Base:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` (production: `https://kamri-server-production.up.railway.app/api` or `https://api.kamrihub.com`)\n- **Locales:** `fr` (French) and `en` (English), all page routes are prefixed with `/{locale}/`\n\n---\n\n## 1. API Route Handlers (Next.js Server-Side -- Network Accessible)\n\nThese are Next.js API route handlers served directly by the application server. They are the TRUE server-side entry points in this codebase.\n\n### 1.1 Public API Endpoints (No Authentication Required)\n\n| Method | Route | File | Line | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/api/analyze-product?id=...` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/analyze-product/route.ts` | 6 | **DEBUG/DIAGNOSTIC** - Analyzes product variants, returns detailed variant extraction data. No auth check. Accepts arbitrary product ID. |\n| GET | `/api/avatar/[...path]` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` | 7 | **IMAGE PROXY** - SSRF-capable proxy for user avatar images. Constructs URLs from user-controlled path segments and fetches from Supabase or upstream server. No auth. Sets `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`. |\n| GET | `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts` | 7 | **IMAGE PROXY** - SSRF-capable proxy for Strapi CMS images. Constructs URLs from user-controlled path and optional `id` query param. No auth. Also queries Strapi API `/api/upload/files/` with user-supplied IDs. Sets `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *`. |\n| GET | `/api/stripe/config` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/stripe/config/route.ts` | 3 | Returns Stripe publishable key. No auth. |\n| GET | `/robots.txt` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/robots.txt/route.ts` | 4 | Serves robots.txt content. |\n| GET | `/sitemap.xml` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/sitemap.xml/route.ts` | 15 | Sitemap index. Calls backend for product counts. |\n| GET | `/sitemap-categories.xml` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/sitemap-categories.xml/route.ts` | 11 | Category sitemap. Calls backend for category data. |\n| GET | `/sitemap-pages.xml` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/sitemap-pages.xml/route.ts` | 12 | Static pages sitemap. |\n| GET | `/sitemap-products-{id}.xml` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/sitemap-products-[id]/route.ts` | 33 | Product sitemap chunks. Calls backend for product data. Accepts `id` parameter from URL. |\n| GET | `/sitemaps.txt` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/sitemaps.txt/route.ts` | 6 | Reads `sitemaps.txt` from filesystem or returns fallback. Uses `fs.readFile` with path from `process.cwd()`. |\n\n### 1.2 Protected API Endpoints\nNone. All Next.js API routes in this codebase are public (no server-side auth middleware on any route handler).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Page Routes (Client-Side Rendered Pages)\n\nAll page routes are under `/[locale]/` (fr or en). Authentication is enforced client-side only (via React context `useAuth`). The middleware handles locale redirects and CSP headers but does NOT enforce authentication on any route.\n\n### 2.1 Public Pages (No Auth Required)\n\n| Route Pattern | File | Description |\n|---------------|------|-------------|\n| `/{locale}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/page.tsx` | Homepage |\n| `/{locale}/products` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/products/page.tsx` | Products listing |\n| `/{locale}/products/categories/{slug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/products/categories/[slug]/page.tsx` | Products by category |\n| `/{locale}/products/subcategory/{externalCategory}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/products/subcategory/[externalCategory]/page.tsx` | Products by subcategory |\n| `/{locale}/product/{slug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/product/[slug]/page.tsx` | Product detail page |\n| `/{locale}/produit/{slug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/produit/[slug]/page.tsx` | Product detail (French alias) |\n| `/{locale}/categories` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/categories/page.tsx` | Categories listing |\n| `/{locale}/categories/{slug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/categories/[slug]/page.tsx` | Category detail |\n| `/{locale}/categories/{slug}/products` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/categories/[slug]/products/page.tsx` | Category products |\n| `/{locale}/{categorySlug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/[categorySlug]/page.tsx` | Dynamic category page |\n| `/{locale}/{categorySlug}/{subcategorySlug}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/[categorySlug]/[subcategorySlug]/page.tsx` | Dynamic subcategory page |\n| `/{locale}/search` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/search/page.tsx` | Search results |\n| `/{locale}/promotions` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/promotions/page.tsx` | Promotions page |\n| `/{locale}/contact` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/contact/page.tsx` | Contact form (sends to backend API `/contact`) |\n| `/{locale}/auth` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/page.tsx` | Login/registration page |\n| `/{locale}/auth/google/callback` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` | Google OAuth callback handler |\n| `/auth/google/callback` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` | Google OAuth callback (no locale) - redirects to locale-prefixed version |\n| `/{locale}/terms` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/terms/page.tsx` | Terms of service |\n| `/{locale}/privacy` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/privacy/page.tsx` | Privacy policy |\n| `/{locale}/legal` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/legal/page.tsx` | Legal information |\n| `/{locale}/legal/cookie-policy` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/legal/cookie-policy/page.tsx` | Cookie policy |\n| `/{locale}/returns` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/returns/page.tsx` | Returns policy |\n| `/{locale}/maintenance` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/maintenance/page.tsx` | Maintenance page |\n| `/{locale}/newsletter/confirm` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/newsletter/confirm/page.tsx` | Newsletter confirmation (calls backend `/newsletter/confirm`) |\n| `/{locale}/compare` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/compare/page.tsx` | Product comparison |\n| `/{locale}/cart` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/cart/page.tsx` | Shopping cart (works without auth for local cart) |\n\n### 2.2 Pages with Client-Side Auth Guards (Soft Protection)\n\nThese pages check `isAuthenticated` in React context and redirect to `/auth?redirect=...` if not authenticated. **This is client-side only -- no server-side enforcement.**\n\n| Route Pattern | File | Line | Auth Check |\n|---------------|------|------|------------|\n| `/{locale}/profile` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/profile/page.tsx` | 34-38 | Redirects to `/auth?redirect=/profile` if not authenticated |\n| `/{locale}/account/orders/{id}` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/account/orders/[id]/page.tsx` | 42-44 | Redirects to `/auth` on 401 response from API |\n| `/{locale}/invoices/{id}/download` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/invoices/[id]/download/page.tsx` | 33-34 | Redirects to `/auth` if not authenticated |\n| `/{locale}/checkout` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/checkout/page.tsx` | 89-91 | Opens auth modal if not authenticated (can be bypassed with guest checkout experiment) |\n| `/{locale}/order-confirmation` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/order-confirmation/page.tsx` | - | Loads order by ID from query param; no strict auth gate |\n| `/{locale}/favorites` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/favorites/page.tsx` | - | Uses wishlist context (fetches via authenticated API), but no explicit redirect guard |\n| `/{locale}/preferences` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/preferences/page.tsx` | 23 | Checks `isAuthenticated` but implementation unclear from first 30 lines |\n\n### 2.3 Admin/Debug Pages\n\n| Route Pattern | File | Line | Description |\n|---------------|------|------|-------------|\n| `/{locale}/admin` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/admin/page.tsx` | 1 | **ADMIN PLACEHOLDER** - No authentication enforcement. Returns placeholder HTML. Layout sets `noindex/nofollow`. |\n| `/{locale}/analyze-product` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/analyze-product/page.tsx` | 7 | **DEBUG TOOL** - Product variant analysis tool. Calls `/api/analyze-product`. No auth required. |\n| `/{locale}/test/maps` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/test/maps/page.tsx` | 7 | **TEST PAGE** - Google Maps Places API test page. Exposes API key presence status. No auth required. |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Middleware\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`\n\n### Middleware Matcher\n```\n/((?!api|_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico).*)\n```\n**IMPORTANT:** The middleware explicitly EXCLUDES `/api` routes, meaning no middleware (CSP, locale redirect, maintenance mode) applies to API route handlers.\n\n### Middleware Functions (in order):\n\n1. **Host redirect (line 109-118):** Production only -- redirects non-www to `www.kamrihub.com` (301)\n2. **Maintenance mode (line 121-169):** If `MAINTENANCE_MODE=true`, redirects all traffic to `/fr/maintenance`. Bypass available via `?bypass=<code>` query param or `maintenance-bypass` cookie. Default bypass code is `dev-bypass-2024` (line 126).\n3. **Sitemap/robots locale redirect (line 174-179):** Redirects `/fr/sitemap*` or `/en/sitemap*` to root sitemap.\n4. **Locale prefix redirect (line 183-189):** Adds `/fr` or `/en` prefix to bare paths based on cookie/Accept-Language/default.\n5. **HTML extension redirect (line 192-195):** 301 redirect for `.html` product URLs.\n6. **Security headers (applied to ALL responses, line 79-87):**\n   - Content-Security-Policy (comprehensive policy)\n   - X-Frame-Options: DENY\n   - X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff\n   - Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin\n   - X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off\n   - Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()\n\n---\n\n## 4. Backend API Calls from Frontend (Via ApiClient)\n\nThe frontend `ApiClient` class (at `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`) makes calls to the backend server. These are NOT entry points of this codebase, but reveal the backend attack surface. The frontend distinguishes between:\n\n- **`fetchPublic()`** -- No auth header, public endpoints\n- **`fetchWithAuth()`** -- Requires Bearer token\n\n### 4.1 Public Backend API Calls (fetchPublic)\n\n| Method | Backend Endpoint | ApiClient Method | Line |\n|--------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| GET | `/products/homepage` | `getHomepageProducts()` | 508 |\n| GET | `/home/new-arrivals` | `getHomeNewArrivals()` | 520 |\n| GET | `/products/top-sales` | `getTopSales()` | 531 |\n| GET | `/products` | `getProductsWithFilters()` | 543 |\n| GET | `/products` | `getProducts()` | 581 |\n| GET | `/products/search` | `searchProducts()` | 593 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/similar` | `getSimilarProducts()` | 661 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/recommended` | `getRecommendedProducts()` | 685 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}` | `getProduct()` | 709 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/reviews` | `getProductReviews()` | 1000 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/check-shipping` | `checkProductShipping()` | 954 |\n| GET | `/categories` | `getCategories()` | 808 |\n| GET | `/categories/with-product-counts` | `getCategoriesWithCounts()` | 814 |\n| GET | `/categories/tree` | `getCategoriesTree()` | 821 |\n| GET | `/categories/{slug}/subcategories` | `getSubcategories()` | 827 |\n| GET | `/geo/detect-country` | `detectCountry()` | 885 |\n| POST | `/geo/set-country` | `setCountry()` | 890 |\n| GET | `/geo/country-name` | `getCountryName()` | 949 |\n| POST | `/visits` | `trackVisit()` | 908 |\n| GET | `/currency/rates` | `getExchangeRates()` | 1063 |\n| GET | `/currency/currency-from-country` | `getCurrencyFromCountry()` | 1074 |\n| GET | `/currency/convert` | `convertPrice()` | 1085 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/products/{id}/reviews` | `getCJProductReviews()` | 976 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/countries/supported` | `getCJSupportedCountries()` | 1410 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/countries` | `getCJCountries()` | 1415 |\n| GET | `/campaigns/active` | `getActiveCampaign()` | 1685 |\n| GET | `/campaigns/active/list` | `getActiveCampaigns()` | 1690 |\n| GET | `/settings/company-info` | `getCompanyInfo()` | 1483 |\n| GET | `/settings/public` | `getPublicSettings()` | 1695 |\n| GET | `/orders/{id}/public` | `getOrderPublic()` | 1256 |\n| POST | `/auth/login` | `login()` | 184 |\n| POST | `/auth/register` | `register()` | 270 |\n| POST | `/auth/request-otp` | `requestOtp()` | 211 |\n| POST | `/auth/verify-otp` | `verifyOtp()` | 235 |\n| POST | `/contact` | `sendContactMessage()` | 1488 |\n\n### 4.2 Authenticated Backend API Calls (fetchWithAuth)\n\n| Method | Backend Endpoint | ApiClient Method | Line |\n|--------|-----------------|-----------------|------|\n| GET | `/users/profile` | `getUserProfile()` | 303 |\n| PUT | `/users/profile` | `updateUserProfile()` | 340 |\n| POST | `/users/profile/avatar` | `uploadUserAvatar()` | 1532 |\n| GET | `/cart` | `getCart()` | 853 |\n| POST | `/cart` | `addToCart()` | 857 |\n| PATCH | `/cart/{id}/quantity` | `updateCartItemQuantity()` | 574 |\n| DELETE | `/cart/{id}` | `removeFromCart()` | 864 |\n| DELETE | `/cart` | `clearCart()` | 870 |\n| POST | `/cart/merge` | `mergeCart()` | 877 |\n| GET | `/cart/grouped` | `getGroupedCart()` | 1095 |\n| GET | `/wishlist` | `getWishlist()` | 1128 |\n| POST | `/wishlist` | `addToWishlist()` | 1132 |\n| DELETE | `/wishlist/{id}` | `removeFromWishlist()` | 1139 |\n| DELETE | `/wishlist` | `clearWishlist()` | 1145 |\n| GET | `/addresses` | `getAddresses()` | 1152 |\n| POST | `/addresses` | `createAddress()` | 1156 |\n| PUT | `/addresses/{id}` | `updateAddress()` | 1174 |\n| DELETE | `/addresses/{id}` | `deleteAddress()` | 1191 |\n| POST | `/addresses/{id}/default` | `setDefaultAddress()` | 1197 |\n| GET | `/user-settings` | `getUserSettings()` | 1204 |\n| PUT | `/user-settings` | `updateUserSettings()` | 1208 |\n| DELETE | `/user-settings/account` | `deleteUserAccount()` | 1233 |\n| GET | `/orders` | `getOrders()` | 1241 |\n| GET | `/orders/pending/latest` | `getLatestPendingOrder()` | 1246 |\n| GET | `/orders/{id}` | `getOrder()` | 1250 |\n| GET | `/orders/by-payment-intent/{id}` | `getOrderByPaymentIntent()` | 1263 |\n| POST | `/orders` | `createOrder()` | 1269 |\n| POST | `/orders/{id}/cancel` | `cancelOrder()` | 1276 |\n| GET | `/orders/tracking-summary` | `getOrdersTrackingSummary()` | 1331 |\n| GET | `/orders/{id}/timeline` | `getOrderTimeline()` | 1341 |\n| GET | `/orders/{id}/trackings` | `getOrderTrackings()` | 1369 |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/my-review` | `getMyReview()` | 1021 |\n| POST | `/products/{id}/reviews` | `createReview()` | 1031 |\n| PATCH | `/reviews/{id}` | `updateReview()` | 1042 |\n| DELETE | `/reviews/{id}` | `deleteReview()` | 1053 |\n| POST | `/categories` | `createCategory()` | 832 |\n| PATCH | `/categories/{id}` | `updateCategory()` | 839 |\n| DELETE | `/categories/{id}` | `deleteCategory()` | 846 |\n| GET | `/settings` | `getSettings()` | 1471 |\n| PUT | `/settings` | `updateSettings()` | 1475 |\n| POST | `/payments/create-intent` | `createPaymentIntent()` | 1572 |\n| GET | `/payments/cards` | `getSavedCards()` | 1592 |\n| DELETE | `/payments/cards/{id}` | `deleteCard()` | 1603 |\n| POST | `/payments/setup-intent` | `createSetupIntent()` | 1610 |\n| POST | `/payments/refund` | `createRefund()` | 1617 |\n| GET | `/payments/refunds/{id}` | `getRefunds()` | 1625 |\n| POST | `/payments/refund/{id}/cancel` | `cancelRefund()` | 1631 |\n| GET | `/invoices/order/{id}` | `getInvoiceByOrderId()` | 1637 |\n| GET | `/invoices/{id}/pdf` | `downloadInvoicePdf()` | 1650 |\n| POST | `/cj-dropshipping/orders/create-v2-auto` | `createCJOrderAuto()` | 1283 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/logistics/track-info` | `getTrackingInfo()` | 1325 |\n| POST | `/cj-dropshipping/logistics/calculate-freight` | `calculateCJFreight()` | 1552 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/products/{id}` | `getDisputeProducts()` | 1421 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/eligibility/{id}` | `getDisputeEligibility()` | 1426 |\n| POST | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/confirm` | `confirmDispute()` | 1430 |\n| POST | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/create` | `createDispute()` | 1437 |\n| POST | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/cancel` | `cancelDispute()` | 1454 |\n| GET | `/cj-dropshipping/disputes/list` | `getDisputes()` | 1461 |\n\n---\n\n## 5. File Upload Endpoints\n\n### 5.1 Contact Form (with attachments)\n- **ApiClient method:** `sendContactMessage()` at `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts` line 1488\n- **Backend endpoint:** `POST /contact`\n- **Auth:** None required (public)\n- **File field:** `attachments` (multiple files via FormData)\n- **No file type/size validation on frontend**\n\n### 5.2 Avatar Upload\n- **ApiClient method:** `uploadUserAvatar()` at `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts` line 1532\n- **Backend endpoint:** `POST /users/profile/avatar`\n- **Auth:** Bearer token required\n- **File field:** `avatar` (single file)\n- **No file type/size validation on frontend**\n\n---\n\n## 6. WebSocket Endpoints\n**None found.** No WebSocket, Socket.IO, or real-time communication endpoints in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Admin/Debug Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | File | Line | Risk |\n|----------|------|------|------|\n| `/{locale}/admin` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/admin/page.tsx` | 1 | **LOW (currently placeholder)** - No auth enforcement. Layout sets noindex/nofollow. |\n| `/{locale}/analyze-product` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/analyze-product/page.tsx` | 7 | **MEDIUM** - Debug tool exposing internal product variant analysis. No auth. |\n| `/api/analyze-product` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/analyze-product/route.ts` | 6 | **MEDIUM** - Server-side API returning detailed variant data for any product ID. No auth. |\n| `/{locale}/test/maps` | `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/test/maps/page.tsx` | 7 | **LOW** - Test page for Google Maps. Reveals whether API key is configured. No auth. |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Webhook Endpoints\n**None in this codebase.** Webhook references in comments indicate Stripe webhooks are handled by the backend server (`kamri-server`), not this frontend.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Health/Status Endpoints\n**None found.** No health check, readiness, or liveness endpoints in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 10. API Schema Files\n**None found.** No OpenAPI/Swagger, GraphQL, gRPC, or JSON Schema files in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Authentication Architecture\n\n### Token Storage\n- **Primary:** In-memory variable (`memoryToken`)\n- **Persistence:** `localStorage` key `auth_token`\n- **Expiry check:** Client-side JWT `exp` claim check via `isJwtExpired()`\n- **File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/secureToken.ts`\n\n### Auth Methods\n1. **Email/Password login** (POST `/auth/login`) -- returns `access_token`\n2. **OTP email login** (POST `/auth/request-otp` -> POST `/auth/verify-otp`) -- returns `access_token`\n3. **Google OAuth** (redirect to backend `/auth/google` -> callback with token in URL/hash)\n4. **Registration** (POST `/auth/register`) -- returns `access_token`\n\n### Auth Enforcement\n- **Server-side (middleware):** NO authentication enforcement. Middleware only handles locale redirects, CSP headers, and maintenance mode.\n- **Client-side:** React `useAuth()` context checks. Pages redirect to `/auth` via `router.push()` or `router.replace()`.\n- **API route handlers:** NONE have authentication checks. All are publicly accessible.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Security Middleware Applied\n\n### CSP Headers (all routes)\nApplied by both `next.config.js` headers() and middleware `addSecurityHeaders()`:\n- `default-src 'self'`\n- `script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'` + Stripe + Google Maps + Google Accounts\n- `img-src 'self' data: https: http:` (very permissive)\n- `connect-src 'self'` + Stripe + API + Google Maps + Railway\n- `frame-src 'self'` + Stripe\n\n### Security Headers\n- `X-Frame-Options: DENY`\n- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`\n- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`\n- `X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off`\n- `Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()`\n\n### Rate Limiting\n- **Frontend-only** soft rate limiter via localStorage timestamps\n- **File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/rateLimiter.ts`\n- Trivially bypassable (client-side only)\n\n### Redirect Safety\n- `safeRedirect()` helper prevents open redirects in auth flow\n- **File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/security/safeRedirect.ts`\n\n---\n\n## 13. Next.js Configuration Security Notes\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/next.config.js`\n\n- **Image optimization:** `remotePatterns` allows ALL hostnames (`hostname: '**'`) for both HTTP and HTTPS (line 21-29). Very permissive.\n- **URL rewrites:** `/sitemap-products-:id.xml` -> `/sitemap-products-:id` (line 8)\n- **Console removal:** Strips `console.log` in production (can be disabled via `ENABLE_DEBUG_LOGS` env var)\n\n---\n\n## 14. Maintenance Mode Bypass\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts` lines 120-168\n\n- Maintenance bypass code defaults to `dev-bypass-2024` (line 126)\n- Bypass via URL param: `?bypass=dev-bypass-2024`\n- Bypass stored in `maintenance-bypass` cookie (httpOnly, 7 days)\n- Google OAuth callback is allowed during maintenance (line 153)\n\n---\n\n## 15. Key Security Observations\n\n1. **SSRF Risk:** `/api/avatar/[...path]` and `/api/strapi-image/[...path]` construct upstream URLs from user-controlled path segments without allowlist validation. An attacker could potentially use these as SSRF proxies.\n\n2. **No Server-Side Auth on API Routes:** All Next.js API route handlers (`/api/*`) are completely unauthenticated. The `/api/analyze-product` endpoint exposes internal product data to anyone.\n\n3. **Debug/Test Pages in Production:** `/analyze-product`, `/test/maps`, and `/admin` pages are accessible without authentication and could leak information.\n\n4. **Maintenance Bypass Hardcoded:** The default bypass code `dev-bypass-2024` is hardcoded and could be guessed.\n\n5. **Permissive Image Configuration:** `next.config.js` allows loading images from any hostname, both HTTP and HTTPS.\n\n6. **Client-Only Auth Guards:** All authentication is enforced client-side via React context. SSR pages serve full HTML before auth checks run. Protected pages can be accessed by anyone who disables JavaScript.\n\n7. **CSP allows unsafe-inline and unsafe-eval:** While necessary for Next.js, this significantly reduces CSP effectiveness against XSS.\n\n8. **Stripe Publishable Key Endpoint:** `/api/stripe/config` exposes the Stripe publishable key (low risk as these are meant to be public, but unnecessary as it could be embedded client-side).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
