[2026-03-21 11:56:10] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 251: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LwoBiMUzMHWmg61T2Ly12X","name":"mcp__shannon-helper__save_deliverable","input":{"deliverable_type":"RECON","content":"# Security Architecture Report -- KamriHub Web (Next.js Frontend)\n\nThis is a comprehensive security-focused code analysis of the KamriHub e-commerce web frontend, a Next.js application. The backend (NestJS) is a separate repository and not analyzed here; findings are limited to the frontend codebase at `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Authentication Endpoints\n\nThe frontend communicates with a backend API. All authentication API calls originate from the `ApiClient` class.\n\n### 1.1 Login (Email/Password -- Legacy)\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 184-208\n\nThe `login` method sends email and password to `POST /api/auth/login`. However, when called from the `AuthContext`, the password is always passed as an empty string (line 262 of `AuthContext.tsx`). This indicates the primary login flow is passwordless (OTP-based), but the legacy password-based endpoint still exists in the API client.\n\n### 1.2 OTP Request (Primary Auth Flow)\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 211-233\n\nSends `POST /api/auth/request-otp` with email and language. Returns a `challengeId` and `expiresAt` timestamp. Has a 10-second client-side timeout via `AbortController`.\n\n### 1.3 OTP Verification\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 235-268\n\nSends `POST /api/auth/verify-otp` with challengeId, email, and code. On success, stores the returned `access_token` via `setAuthToken()`. Has a 10-second client-side timeout.\n\n### 1.4 Registration\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 270-294\n\nSends `POST /api/auth/register` with email, name, password, and `role: 'user'` as a client-controlled parameter (line 277). If the backend does not validate/ignore this parameter, a malicious user could potentially set `role: 'admin'`.\n\n### 1.5 Logout\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 296-300\n\nLogout is client-side only. There is no server-side call to invalidate the token/session. The token is cleared from memory and localStorage.\n\n### 1.6 Google OAuth (SSO)\n\n- Initiation: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx`, line 176 -- redirects to `{API_BASE_URL}/auth/google`\n- Callback (no locale): `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` -- server-side redirect to locale-prefixed version\n- Callback (with locale): `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` -- extracts token from URL query/hash, stores it\n\n### 1.7 Profile Operations\n\n- GET profile: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 303-338 -- `GET /api/users/profile` with Bearer token\n- Update profile: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 340-370 -- `PUT /api/users/profile`\n- Delete account: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 1233-1237 -- `DELETE /api/user-settings/account`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Authentication Mechanisms\n\n### 2.1 Token Type: JWT Bearer Token\n\nAll authenticated API calls include `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, line 457\n\n### 2.2 Token Storage\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/secureToken.ts`, lines 1-123\n\nDual-layer: in-memory variable (line 20) + localStorage (key: `auth_token`, line 34). The in-memory approach provides minimal additional security since the token is always written to localStorage.\n\n### 2.3 JWT Expiration Check (Client-side)\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/security/jwt.ts`, lines 1-15\n\nDecodes JWT payload via `atob()`, checks `exp` claim. No signature verification (by design). Tokens without `exp` are treated as valid indefinitely.\n\n### 2.4 Session Duration\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx`, line 14 -- 24 hours max (`SESSION_MAX_DURATION`)\n\nPeriodic check every 60 seconds (line 182). Cross-tab synchronization via `storage` event (lines 203-218).\n\n### 2.5 401 Handling\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/api.ts`, lines 479-486 -- Clears token and dispatches `auth:unauthorized` event on HTTP 401.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Session Management\n\n### 3.1 Cookie Configuration\n\n**Maintenance bypass cookie:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`, lines 137-142\n- httpOnly: true, secure: conditional (production only), sameSite: lax, maxAge: 7 days\n\n**Locale cookie:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`, line 187\n- No httpOnly, no secure, no sameSite, maxAge: 1 year\n\n**Language cookies via document.cookie:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/contexts/LanguageContext.tsx`, lines 91-93, 158\n- No Secure, HttpOnly, or SameSite flags\n\n### 3.2 Auth Token Storage\n\nlocalStorage key `auth_token` + in-memory variable. No HttpOnly cookie protection.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Authorization Model\n\n### 4.1 No Frontend Authorization\n\n- Admin layout has no auth check: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/admin/layout.tsx`\n- Profile layout has no auth guard: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/profile/layout.tsx`\n- Checkout layout has no auth guard: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/[locale]/checkout/layout.tsx`\n- No route-level middleware checks for authentication status\n- Authorization entirely enforced server-side\n\n### 4.2 API Call Separation\n\n- `fetchPublic()` (line 377) -- no auth, for public data\n- `fetchWithAuth()` (line 439) -- Bearer token, guards against missing token (line 441)\n\n---\n\n## 5. SSO / OAuth / OIDC\n\n### 5.1 Google OAuth\n\nFull flow: frontend redirect -> backend `/auth/google` -> Google -> backend callback -> frontend `/auth/google/callback?token=...`\n\n### 5.2 State Parameter\n\nBackend validates state parameter (error reason 'state' handled in callback). Frontend does not generate/validate state.\n\n### 5.3 Nonce Parameter\n\nNo nonce parameter generation or validation found anywhere in the codebase.\n\n### 5.4 Token via URL\n\nToken transported via URL query parameter and hash fragment. Risk of logging by proxies, browser history, Referrer headers.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Security Middleware\n\n### 6.1 CSP\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`, lines 34-76\n\nIncludes `'unsafe-inline'` and `'unsafe-eval'` in script-src. `img-src` allows any HTTP/HTTPS source.\n\n### 6.2 Security Headers\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/middleware.ts`, lines 79-87\n\nPresent: X-Frame-Options DENY, X-Content-Type-Options nosniff, Referrer-Policy, X-DNS-Prefetch-Control, Permissions-Policy.\nMissing: Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS).\n\n### 6.3 Open Redirect Protection\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/security/safeRedirect.ts`, lines 1-18 -- Good implementation.\n\n### 6.4 Rate Limiting\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/rateLimiter.ts` -- Client-side only, localStorage-based, trivially bypassable.\n\n### 6.5 CSRF\n\nNo CSRF protection. Auth uses Bearer tokens (not auto-sent cookies), so authenticated endpoints have inherent protection. Unauthenticated action endpoints lack protection.\n\n### 6.6 CORS\n\nWildcard `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` on image proxy routes:\n- `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts`, line 89\n- `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts`, line 218\n\n---\n\n## 7. Input Validation\n\n### 7.1 HTML Sanitization\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/sanitize.ts` -- DOMPurify + regex fallback. Regex fallback is fragile.\n\n### 7.2 Text/Address Validation\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/validation.ts` -- Regex validators for phone, city, state, zip, country, street.\n\n### 7.3 Anti-Spam\n\n**File:** `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/utils/antiSpam.ts` -- Email validation, timing checks, honeypot, spam keyword detection.\n\n### 7.4 dangerouslySetInnerHTML\n\nFound in 4 locations, all for JSON-LD structured data (safe usage via JSON.stringify).\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cryptographic Implementations\n\n- JWT parsing only (no signature verification): `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/lib/security/jwt.ts`\n- No client-side password hashing, encryption, or key management\n- Passwordless (OTP) authentication -- no passwords stored\n\n---\n\n## 9. Image Proxy Routes (SSRF Risk)\n\n- Avatar proxy: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` -- unvalidated path segments\n- Strapi proxy: `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web/src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts` -- unvalidated path segments\n\n---\n\n## 10. Environment Variable Exposure\n\n- `.env` contains Supabase service_role key (line 15), Stripe test key (line 21), maintenance bypass code (line 32), Google Maps API key (line 34), Strapi license (line 39)\n- `.gitignore` excludes .env files (lines 26-27)\n- Hardcoded production URLs in source code: `src/lib/server-api.ts` line 23, `src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` line 50\n- Default maintenance bypass code hardcoded: `src/middleware.ts` line 126\n\n---\n\n## 11. Next.js Configuration\n\n- Wildcard remote image patterns (HTTP+HTTPS, any hostname): `next.config.js` lines 20-29\n- Console logs removed in production (except console.error): `next.config.js` lines 13-16\n\n---\n\n## 12. Security Weaknesses Summary\n\n| # | Severity | Finding | File | Line(s) |\n|---|----------|---------|------|---------|\n| 1 | HIGH | Auth token in localStorage (XSS-accessible) | src/lib/secureToken.ts | 34 |\n| 2 | HIGH | CSP unsafe-inline + unsafe-eval in script-src | src/middleware.ts | 66-67 |\n| 3 | HIGH | No HSTS header | src/middleware.ts | 79-87 |\n| 4 | HIGH | Supabase service_role key in frontend .env | .env | 15 |\n| 5 | HIGH | Hardcoded default maintenance bypass code | src/middleware.ts | 126 |\n| 6 | MEDIUM | Registration sends client-controlled role | src/lib/api.ts | 277 |\n| 7 | MEDIUM | No server-side logout / token invalidation | src/lib/api.ts | 296-300 |\n| 8 | MEDIUM | OAuth token via URL query/hash | src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx | 16-37 |\n| 9 | MEDIUM | Wildcard image remote patterns | next.config.js | 20-29 |\n| 10 | MEDIUM | No CSRF protection | (codebase-wide) | N/A |\n| 11 | MEDIUM | Image proxy SSRF risk (unvalidated paths) | src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts | 15 |\n| 12 | MEDIUM | Image proxy SSRF risk (unvalidated paths) | src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts | 15 |\n| 13 | MEDIUM | Wildcard CORS on proxy routes | src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts | 89 |\n| 14 | LOW | Client-side-only rate limiting | src/lib/rateLimiter.ts | 17-36 |\n| 15 | LOW | No frontend admin route auth guards | src/app/[locale]/admin/layout.tsx | 15-17 |\n| 16 | LOW | No nonce-based CSP | src/middleware.ts | 63 |\n| 17 | LOW | Fragile regex HTML sanitization fallback | src/utils/sanitize.ts | 44-58 |\n| 18 | LOW | Locale cookies without Secure/HttpOnly | src/contexts/LanguageContext.tsx | 91-93 |\n| 19 | INFO | JWT exp check treats missing exp as not expired | src/lib/security/jwt.ts | 10 |\n| 20 | INFO | Hardcoded production API URLs | src/lib/server-api.ts | 23 |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
