[2026-03-21 11:59:11] [pre-recon] [LLM] Turn 270: {"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017FXYq2ob9tnnGEnkhxNymx","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Data Security Auditor Agent","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"You are a Data Security Auditor Agent performing security-focused code analysis on a Next.js e-commerce frontend application located at `/repos/KamriHub/kamri-web`.\n\n**APPLICATION CONTEXT:** This is a Next.js 14 App Router e-commerce frontend. It communicates with:\n- NestJS backend on Railway (kamri-server-production.up.railway.app)\n- Strapi CMS (for campaigns/content)\n- Supabase (for avatar storage, with service_role key found in .env)\n- Stripe (for payments)\n- Google OAuth (for SSO login)\n- Google Maps (for address autocomplete)\n\n**YOUR TASKS:**\n\n1. **Trace sensitive data flows:**\n   - Personal Identifiable Information (PII): names, emails, addresses, phone numbers\n   - Payment data: credit card handling, Stripe integration\n   - Authentication tokens: where they flow, how they're stored, where they're transmitted\n   - Passwords: where they appear (even if passwordless OTP is primary)\n\n2. **Analyze token security:**\n   - Read `/src/lib/secureToken.ts` in detail\n   - Trace token lifecycle: creation → storage → usage → expiration → deletion\n   - Assess XSS exposure of tokens in localStorage\n\n3. **Analyze Stripe integration:**\n   - How payment data is handled\n   - Is card data ever transmitted to the application server?\n   - Stripe publishable key exposure\n   - Client-side Stripe Elements usage\n\n4. **Analyze Supabase integration:**\n   - Find ALL Supabase client usage\n   - Check if the service_role key is ever exposed to the browser\n   - Assess what operations are possible with the exposed keys\n\n5. **Analyze Google Maps integration:**\n   - API key exposure\n   - What APIs are enabled for the key\n   - Rate limiting concerns\n\n6. **Analyze form data handling:**\n   - Contact form data flow\n   - Registration form data flow\n   - Profile update data flow\n   - Address/checkout data flow\n   - File upload data flow (avatars, contact attachments)\n\n7. **Check for data leakage:**\n   - Console logging of sensitive data\n   - Error messages exposing internals\n   - API responses leaking sensitive fields\n   - Browser storage (localStorage, sessionStorage) of sensitive data\n\n8. **Analyze environment variable exposure:**\n   - Which env vars are prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ (exposed to browser)?\n   - Are any server-only secrets accidentally exposed?\n   - Read .env files for committed secrets\n\n9. **Check GDPR/Privacy compliance:**\n   - Cookie consent implementation\n   - Data deletion mechanisms\n   - Privacy policy references in code\n\n10. **Analyze multi-tenancy/data isolation:**\n    - Is there any multi-tenant data separation?\n    - Can one user access another user's data through API calls?\n\n**For each finding, provide:**\n- Exact file path and line number(s)\n- The sensitive data type involved\n- The security concern\n- Risk assessment (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)\n\nBe thorough and systematic in tracing every data flow.","max_turns":30},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
