| `src/app/robots.txt/route.ts` | SEO robots file | INFO |\n| `/sitemap.xml` | GET | `src/app/sitemap.xml/route.ts` | SEO sitemap | INFO |\n| `/sitemap-categories.xml` | GET | `src/app/sitemap-categories.xml/route.ts` | Category sitemap | INFO |\n| `/sitemap-pages.xml` | GET | `src/app/sitemap-pages.xml/route.ts` | Pages sitemap | INFO |\n| `/sitemap-products-[id].xml` | GET | `src/app/sitemap-products-[id].xml/route.ts` | Product sitemaps | INFO |\n\n**Page Routes with Security Relevance:**\n\n| Route | Auth Required | File | Security Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `/[locale]/auth/google/callback` | No | `src/app/[locale]/auth/google/callback/page.tsx` | Token extraction from URL, PII logging |\n| `/[locale]/admin` | **None (no guard)** | `src/app/[locale]/admin/page.tsx` | Placeholder admin page, no auth check |\n| `/[locale]/analyze-product` | **None** | Page route | Debug tool exposed without auth |\n| `/[locale]/test/maps` | **None** | Page route | Test page exposed without auth |\n| `/[locale]/profile/*` | Client-side only | `src/app/[locale]/profile/layout.tsx` | useAuth() guard, bypassable |\n| `/[locale]/checkout/*` | Client-side only | `src/app/[locale]/checkout/layout.tsx` | useAuth() guard, bypassable |\n| `/[locale]/order-confirmation` | Client-side only | `src/app/[locale]/order-confirmation/page.tsx` | orderId from URL params |\n| `/[locale]/contact` | No | Contact form | File upload via backend, anti-spam |\n\n### Internal Service Communication\n\nThe frontend communicates with the following external services, all over HTTPS:\n\n1. **Backend API** (`kamri-server-production.up.railway.app/api`): All authenticated and business logic requests. Hardcoded fallback URL at `src/lib/server-api.ts` line 23 and `src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` line 50.\n2. **Strapi CMS** (configurable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL`): Campaign and content data fetched server-side via `src/lib/strapi.ts`.\n3. **Supabase** (configurable via `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`): Avatar storage. The avatar proxy route can redirect to Supabase URLs.\n4. **Stripe** (via `stripe.js` CDN): Payment processing entirely within Stripe's iframe context.\n5. **Google Maps** (via Maps JavaScript API): Address autocomplete in checkout flow.\n6. **Google OAuth** (via backend redirect): SSO authentication delegation.\n\n**Trust assumption vulnerability:** The proxy routes (`/api/avatar/`, `/api/strapi-image/`) trust the path segments from the URL without validation, and the backend/Strapi/Supabase URLs are constructed by concatenation. This creates SSRF opportunities to redirect these server-side fetches to arbitrary destinations.\n\n### Input Validation Patterns\n\nInput validation is inconsistently applied across the application:\n\n- **Strong:** `safeRedirect()` at `src/lib/security/safeRedirect.ts` properly validates redirect URLs (blocks absolute URLs, protocol-relative URLs, non-path redirects). Used in auth page and AuthModal.\n- **Strong:** Address/profile fields use `sanitizeText()` and regex validators from `src/utils/validation.ts` (phone, city, state, zip, country, street).\n- **Strong:** Anti-spam on contact form via `src/utils/antiSpam.ts` (honeypot, timing check, spam keyword detection, URL detection).\n- **Weak:** HTML sanitization at `src/utils/sanitize.ts` references DOMPurify but it's not installed; regex fallback is fragile. **Not called anywhere in the codebase** — review comments bypass sanitization entirely.\n- **Weak:** Rate limiting at `src/lib/rateLimiter.ts` is localStorage-based and trivially bypassable (acknowledged in code comment at line 5).\n- **Missing:** No server-side input validation on any Next.js API route handler. No path validation on proxy routes.\n- **Missing:** `safeRedirect()` is NOT applied to Google OAuth return URL stored in sessionStorage (`src/components/AuthModal.tsx` line 731).\n\n### Background Processing\n\nThe application uses no background job processing on the frontend. All asynchronous operations (order processing, email sending, etc.) are handled by the backend API. The frontend does have:\n- **Periodic session check:** Every 60 seconds, the AuthContext checks if the session has exceeded 24 hours (`src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` line 182).\n- **Cross-tab synchronization:** localStorage `storage` event listener detects token changes across browser tabs (`src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` lines 203-218).\n- **Contact form auto-draft:** Saves form data to localStorage every 2 seconds (`src/components/ContactForm.tsx` line 48).\n\n### Notable Out-of-Scope Components\n\n- **`@kamri/lib` package:** Shared types, Zod schemas, and API types. Build-time dependency only.\n- **`@kamri/ui` package:** Shared React UI components. Build-time dependency only.\n- **Vitest/Playwright:** Test frameworks, not network-accessible.\n- **ESLint:** Linting tool, development only.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Infrastructure & Operational Security\n\n### Secrets Management\n\nSecrets management follows a **minimal approach** with significant risks:\n\n- **`.env` file** contains all secrets including the Supabase service_role JWT. While `.gitignore` excludes `.env` and `.env*.local`, the presence of `.env` in the working directory (and `.env.local` with committed Google Maps API key) indicates secrets are managed via environment files rather than a dedicated secrets manager.\n- **No secrets rotation mechanism** is visible in the codebase.\n- **Hardcoded fallback secrets:** The maintenance bypass code defaults to `dev-bypass-2024` if the environment variable is not set (`src/middleware.ts` line 126). The backend API URL defaults to the production Railway URL if `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` is not set (`src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` line 50, `src/lib/server-api.ts` line 23).\n- **Vercel deployment** likely uses Vercel Environment Variables for production, but the local `.env` file pattern creates risk of accidental secret exposure.\n\n### Configuration Security\n\n**Security Headers (three inconsistent sources):**\n\n1. **Edge Middleware** (`src/middleware.ts` lines 79-87): CSP, X-Frame-Options: DENY, X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff, Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin, X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off, Permissions-Policy\n2. **next.config.js** (lines 44-106): CSP headers (includes `accounts.google.com` which middleware CSP lacks)\n3. **vercel.json**: CSP headers (missing Google Maps in connect-src), X-XSS-Protection\n\n**Critical gaps:**\n- **No `Strict-Transport-Security` (HSTS) header** anywhere in the configuration. This is a significant omission for a production e-commerce site handling payment data.\n- **No `Cache-Control` security headers** for sensitive responses.\n- **Three inconsistent CSP definitions** create confusion about which policy actually applies. The middleware CSP includes `'unsafe-inline'` and `'unsafe-eval'` in `script-src` (line 66), effectively neutralizing XSS protection.\n- **CSP `img-src` allows `http:`** — images can be loaded over unencrypted HTTP.\n- **No Nginx, Kubernetes Ingress, or CDN configuration** found in the codebase (Vercel handles edge infrastructure).\n\n**CORS Configuration:**\n- **`vercel.json`** sets wide-open CORS on `/api/*` paths.\n- **Proxy routes** explicitly set `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` on responses (`src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` line 89, `src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts` line 218).\n- This allows any origin to make requests to these SSRF-vulnerable proxy endpoints.\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Service | Purpose | Security Consideration |\n|---|---|---|\n| Railway (NestJS backend) | Business logic, auth, data storage | All authorization depends on this service |\n| Vercel | Frontend hosting, edge middleware | Manages CDN, SSL termination, edge functions |\n| Supabase | Avatar storage | Service_role key in `.env` grants full admin access |\n| Strapi CMS | Campaigns, content | API integration via server-side proxy |\n| Stripe | Payments | Properly delegated to Stripe.js; publishable key only |\n| Google OAuth | SSO | Backend handles OAuth flow; token via URL |\n| Google Maps | Address autocomplete | API key browser-exposed; needs domain restriction |\n| CJDropshipping | Product data, reviews | Product reviews rendered with innerHTML (XSS risk) |\n\n### Monitoring & Logging\n\n- **Logger utility** (`src/utils/logger.ts`): Only outputs in development mode (`NODE_ENV === 'development'`). However, many files use raw `console.log` instead, which runs in production. Notable production console.log calls:\n  - Google OAuth callback: 11 calls including PII (userId, email) at line 200\n  - GoogleCallbackRedirectGuard: 1 call with redirect URL\n  - AddressSectionNew: 2 calls\n  - secureToken.ts: 4 error-level calls\n- **No structured logging, error tracking (Sentry/Datadog), or security event monitoring** detected.\n- **next.config.js** removes all `console.*` except `console.error` in production builds (lines 13-16), BUT this only applies to client-side code bundled by webpack. Server-side console calls in API routes may still execute."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
