*\n\n- **Files:** `src/app/api/avatar/[...path]/route.ts` (line 55), `src/app/api/strapi-image/[...path]/route.ts` (lines 37, 65, 89, 123)\n- All server-side `fetch()` calls in the proxy routes use `redirect: 'follow'`, enabling redirect-chain SSRF bypass even if hostname validation were added in the future.\n- No DNS resolution pinning in any proxy route, making future hostname-based validation vulnerable to DNS rebinding attacks.\n\n---\n\n### Analyzed and Cleared Endpoints (No SSRF Risk)\n\n| Endpoint/File | Assessment |\n|---|---|\n| `/api/stripe/config` (`route.ts`) | Returns env var only, no outbound requests. **No SSRF.** |\n| `/api/analyze-product` (`route.ts`) | Uses `apiClient.getProduct()` with server-configured base URL. ProductId is user-controlled but only used as query parameter. **Minimal SSRF risk.** |\n| `src/lib/server-api.ts` (serverFetch) | All requests to server-configured `API_BASE_URL`. Endpoint paths hardcoded. Query parameters properly serialized via `URLSearchParams`. **No SSRF.** |\n| `src/lib/strapi.ts` (StrapiService) | Requests to server-configured Strapi URL. Endpoints hardcoded (`/campaigns`). Filter values parameterized. **No SSRF.** |\n| `src/lib/api.ts` (ApiClient) | Client-side only. All requests to fixed `API_BASE_URL`. User input in request bodies/query params only. **No SSRF.** |\n| `src/lib/security/safeRedirect.ts` | Properly validates redirect URLs. Blocks absolute URLs, protocol-relative URLs. **No open redirect.** |\n\n---\n\n### SSRF Attack Chain Summary\n\nThe most dangerous attack chain combines SSRF findings with credential exposure:\n\n1. **SSRF via proxy routes** → Probe internal Vercel/Railway infrastructure\n2. **SSRF + exposed Supabase service_role key** → If SSRF can reach Supabase REST API, the attacker has full database admin access\n3. **`/_next/image` universal proxy** → Cloud metadata access (AWS/GCP instance credentials)\n4. **All proxy routes have `CORS: *`** → Any malicious website can trigger SSRF via cross-origin requests"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}
